# LEGAL COMMAND CENTER — Autonomous CRM Protocol

## Overview

The Fortress Legal Command Center is an autonomous multi-case litigation CRM integrated into the Batch Classifier dashboard and backed by a dedicated PostgreSQL schema (`legal.*`). It provides:
- **Case Management** — CRUD for cases, deadlines, evidence, watchdog terms
- **Correspondence Engine** — Draft, approve, and track all legal communications
- **Document Generator** — Template-driven court filings and formal letters
- **Gmail Integration** — Push approved correspondence to Gmail as drafts (human reviews and sends)
- **Deadline Monitor** — Autonomous cron-based alerting for upcoming/overdue deadlines
- **Correspondence Watch** — Auto-detect replies from opposing parties

## Architecture

### Database Schema: `legal.*`

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `legal.cases` | Case registry — one row per case with all metadata |
| `legal.case_actions` | Timeline — every action taken on a case (email, mail, filing, etc.) |
| `legal.case_watchdog` | Search terms — monitored senders, subjects, body phrases per case |
| `legal.case_evidence` | Evidence index — emails, documents, receipts linked to cases |
| `legal.correspondence` | CRM memory — all inbound/outbound communications with status tracking |
| `legal.deadlines` | Deadline tracking — due dates, extensions, alert thresholds, urgency |

### NAS Structure

Each case gets a directory at `/mnt/fortress_nas/sectors/legal/{case_slug}/`:
```
/mnt/fortress_nas/sectors/legal/{case_slug}/
├── evidence/           # Forensic reports, evidence CSVs, email exports
├── correspondence/     # Letters, emails (draft + sent), formal requests
├── certified_mail/     # Print packages, USPS receipts, green cards (scanned)
└── filings/
    ├── incoming/       # Complaints, motions from opposing party
    └── outgoing/       # Our motions, answers, generated documents
```

### Services

| Service | Port | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Batch Classifier (Legal CRM + Legal Hold tabs) | 9877 | Primary UI — CRM dashboard, case selector, deadline dashboard, correspondence timeline, document vault |
| Legal Case Manager + CRM API | 9878 | Full CRUD API — cases, actions, evidence, watchdog, correspondence, deadlines, document generation, Gmail draft integration |
| Legal CRM Watchdog (cron) | N/A | Every 2h: email archive scan + deadline monitor + correspondence reply detection |

### API Endpoints (Port 9878)

**Case Management:**
- `GET /api/cases` — List all cases
- `GET /api/cases/{slug}` — Full case detail with actions, evidence, watchdog
- `POST /api/cases` — Register new case
- `GET /api/crm/overview` — Full CRM dashboard data (cases, deadlines, correspondence, actions)

**Correspondence:**
- `GET /api/cases/{slug}/correspondence` — List correspondence for a case
- `POST /api/cases/{slug}/correspondence` — Create correspondence draft
- `PUT /api/correspondence/{id}/approve` — Approve draft for sending
- `PUT /api/correspondence/{id}/mark-sent` — Mark as sent (with optional tracking number)
- `POST /api/correspondence/{id}/create-gmail-draft` — Push to Gmail as draft

**Deadlines:**
- `GET /api/cases/{slug}/deadlines` — List deadlines with countdown and urgency
- `POST /api/cases/{slug}/deadlines` — Add a deadline
- `PUT /api/deadlines/{id}` — Update deadline (extend, complete, etc.)
- `GET /api/deadlines/all` — All active deadlines across all cases

**Documents:**
- `GET /api/cases/{slug}/documents` — List all files on NAS for a case
- `GET /api/templates` — List available document templates
- `POST /api/cases/{slug}/generate/{template}` — Generate document from template, save to NAS

**Templates Available:**
- `court_caption` — Standard Georgia Superior Court caption block
- `motion_extension` — Motion for Extension of Time
- `answer_complaint` — Answer to Complaint with affirmative defenses
- `correspondence_formal` — Formal letter to opposing counsel
- `demand_letter` — Settlement/demand letter (Rule 408 protected)
- `email_opposing_counsel` — Email body for Gmail draft
- `certificate_of_service` — Standalone Certificate of Service
- `attorney_briefing` — Case summary briefing package

## MANDATORY RULES

### 1. Case Registration Protocol

**Every legal case MUST be registered before any code touches it:**

```python
# Register via API
POST /api/cases
{
    "case_slug": "prime-trust-23-11161",      # URL-friendly unique ID
    "case_number": "23-11161-JKS",            # Official case number
    "case_name": "Prime Core Technologies d/b/a Prime Trust",
    "court": "USBC District of Delaware",
    "case_type": "bankruptcy",                 # bankruptcy, class_action, civil, regulatory
    "our_role": "creditor",                    # creditor, plaintiff, defendant, claimant
    "critical_date": "2026-03-12",
    "plan_admin_email": "don.detweiler@wbd-us.com"
}
```

### 2. Correspondence Protocol (CRM Workflow)

All outbound legal communications follow a strict workflow:

1. **DRAFT** — Create via API or dashboard. Saved to `legal.correspondence`.
2. **APPROVE** — Human reviews and approves via dashboard button.
3. **GMAIL DRAFT** — Push to Gmail (optional). Creates a draft the human sends.
4. **SENT** — Marked as sent after human confirms delivery.
5. **REPLY DETECTED** — Watchdog auto-detects inbound replies and logs them.

**Rules:**
- **NEVER auto-send** — All outbound correspondence requires human approval
- **Gmail scope is `compose` only** — physically cannot send without human action
- **Every communication logged** — All correspondence tracked in `legal.correspondence`
- **Audit trail** — Every action auto-logged to `legal.case_actions`

### 3. Evidence Preservation Protocol

- **Never delete emails** that are linked to active legal cases
- **Every document generated** (forensic reports, letters, motions) MUST be saved to NAS
- **SHA-256 hash** every generated document for tamper-proofing
- **Timestamp everything** with UTC ISO 8601
- **Certified mail receipts** must be scanned and saved to `certified_mail/`

### 4. Deadline Management Protocol

- **Every case MUST have deadlines** in `legal.deadlines`
- **Urgency levels** — overdue (red), critical (<=3 days), urgent (<=7), warning (<=14), normal
- **Watchdog monitors deadlines** every 2 hours via cron
- **P0 alerts** for overdue deadlines, **P1** for critical/urgent
- **Extensions tracked** — `extended_to` field with `extension_reason`
- **Missed deadlines** auto-marked by watchdog when overdue with no extension

### 5. Document Generation Rules

When generating legal documents:
- **Use the template engine** — `POST /api/cases/{slug}/generate/{template}`
- **All documents saved to NAS** with timestamp in filename
- **SHA-256 hash included** in every generated document
- **Use formal legal formatting** — case captions, docket references, proper citations
- **Always include a Certificate of Service** in court filings
- **Templates pull from case data** — no hardcoded party names

### 6. Watchdog Rules

The watchdog cron (`tools/kyc_watchdog.py`) runs three scans every 2 hours:

| Scan | Function | Alerts |
|---|---|---|
| Email Archive | Searches watchdog terms against 57K+ emails | P1-CRITICAL, P2-INVESTIGATE |
| Deadline Monitor | Checks `legal.deadlines` for approaching/overdue items | P0-OVERDUE, P0-TODAY, P1-CRITICAL, P1-URGENT |
| Correspondence Watch | Detects replies to sent outbound communications | Auto-links to `legal.correspondence` |

- **Every case MUST have watchdog terms** in `legal.case_watchdog`
- **Prioritize terms**: P1 (critical — direct from opposing party), P2 (important), P3 (monitoring)
- **False positive filtering**: Use high-specificity terms only
- **Alerts written** to `sentinel_alerts` table (if exists) for P0/P1

### 7. Golden Rules Integration

For each legal case:
- **Add vendor patterns** to `finance.classification_rules` with `LITIGATION_RECOVERY` category
- **Include all known entity names**: opposing counsel, fiduciary agents, collection agencies
- **Use `CFO-LITIGATION` as `created_by`** for all litigation golden rules

### 8. Adding a New Legal Case (Checklist)

When the user says they have a new legal case:

1. **Gather case metadata**: case number, court, parties, our role, key dates
2. **Register the case**: `POST /api/cases` with all available metadata
3. **Create NAS directories**: `mkdir -p /mnt/fortress_nas/sectors/legal/{slug}/...`
4. **Add deadlines**: `POST /api/cases/{slug}/deadlines` for all known dates
5. **Add watchdog terms**: All known senders, subjects, body phrases for the opposing party
6. **Inject golden rules**: Add entity names to `finance.classification_rules`
7. **Run initial forensic scan**: Search 57K+ emails for any existing correspondence
8. **Index existing evidence**: Link any discovered emails to `legal.case_evidence`
9. **Generate documents**: Use template engine for motions, answers, briefings
10. **Create correspondence**: Draft any needed outbound communications
11. **Update this file**: Add the case to the Active Cases table below

